0large%20developed%20business%20to%20leading%20a%20smaller%20activity.%20My%20first%20reaction%20was%20to%20simply%20ask%3A%20Why%20would%20I%20trade%20a%20large%20opportunity%20for%20what%20seemed%20like%20a%20smaller%20one%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20co-head%20of%20my%20division%20at%20the%20time%20and%20the%20champion%20for%20this%20career%20move%20was%20David%20Solomon%2C%20who%20also%20happens%20to%20be%20my%20current%20boss%2C%20and%20he%20was%20quick%20to%20point%20out%20that%20I%20was%20looking%20at%20the%20opportunity%20the%20wrong%20way.%20It%20was%20not%20about%20trading%20from%20a%20big%20business%20to%20a%20small%20business%20but%20rather%20seizing%20an%20opportunity%20that%20could%20make%20a%20meaningful%20difference%20for%20the%20firm.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHis%20guidance%20reframed%20my%20thinking.%20I%20moved%20to%20London%2C%20and%20over%20the%20ensuing%20years%20for%20a%20variety%20of%20reasons%2C%20our%20European%20financing%20business%20grew%20significantly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20push%20to%20move%20to%20London%20was%20not%20only%20a%20great%20career%20move%20for%20me%2C%20but%20also%20enhanced%20our%20ability%20to%20compete%20in%20EMEA.%20The%20lesson%20was%20equally%20important%3A%20Trust%20the%20firm%2C%20trust%20the%20people%20you%20work%20with%2C%20and%20be%20willing%20to%20take%20risks%20with%20your%20career.%20That's%20how%20you%20end%20up%20making%20a%20difference.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20was%20a%20junior%20analyst%20at%20Goldman%20Sachs%2C%20I%20was%20given%20a%20piece%20of%20tactical%20advice%20that%20would%20shape%20how%20I%20looked%20at%20career%20development%3A%20If%20you%20are%20looking%20to%20accelerate%20your%20career%2C%20identify%20the%20aspects%20of%20your%20boss's%20job%20or%20the%20tasks%20they%20are%20responsible%20for%20that%20don't%20necessarily%20require%20their%20personal%20oversight%2C%20and%20offer%20to%20take%20on%20the%20responsibility.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20will%20free%20your%20manager%20from%20some%20of%20their%20less%20strategic%20tasks%2C%20enabling%20them%20to%20spend%20more%20time%20and%20energy%20on%20the%20things%20that%20benefit%20the%20business%20the%20most.%20In%20addition%2C%20as%20a%20more%20junior%20party%2C%20taking%20on%20these%20responsibilities%20will%20give%20you%20an%20opportunity%20to%20gain%20exposure%20to%20things%20that%20a%20more%20senior%20person%20is%20usually%20tasked%20with.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20need%20to%20work%20hard%20and%20do%20your%20job%20with%20excellence%2C%20but%20you%20can%20separate%20yourself%20by%20volunteering%20to%20take%20on%20more%20to%20develop%20your%20skills%20and%20free%20up%20the%20time%20of%20those%20above%20you.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%224fdaaf9a-d935-4f19-8def-abb70130fe46%5C%22%3ELauren%20Belmonte%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EFirm%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EMorgan%20Stanley%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ETitle%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EHead%20of%20technology%20equity%20capital%20markets%20in%20the%20Americas%2C%20managing%20director%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Morgan%20Stanley's%20Lauren%20Belmonte.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F683de598ca50259add4d74ed%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221125%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMorgan%20Stanley's%20head%20of%20technology%20equity%20capital%20markets%20in%20the%20Americas%2C%20Lauren%20Belmonte.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Morgan%20Stanley%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20started%20working%20at%20Morgan%20Stanley%20as%20an%20associate%20out%20of%20business%20school%2C%20I%20had%20the%20fortunate%20opportunity%20to%20partner%20with%20Jim%20Runde%20%E2%80%94%20a%20legendary%20banker%20on%20Wall%20Street%20with%20a%20multi-decade%20career.%20I%20met%20him%20at%20the%20stage%20in%20his%20career%20where%20he%20was%20focused%20on%20developing%20talent%20across%20our%20investment%20banking%20teams.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20our%20regular%20coffee%20catchups%2C%20he%20would%20share%20very%20