l%20money%3F%20The%20appeal%20is%20that%20they're%20cheap%20to%20make%2C%20but%20how%20big%20of%20a%20business%20can%20they%20be%3F%20And%20what's%20the%20right%20mix%20of%20revenue%20between%20ads%20and%20viewer%20payments%3F%20ReelShort%20parent%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freelshort-taking-on-hollywood-short-dramas-courts-creators-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECrazy%20Maple%20Studio's%20founder%20Joey%20Jia%20said%3C%2Fa%3E%20last%20year%20that%20viewers%20typically%20paid%20%245%20to%20%2410%20a%20week.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHow%20should%20they%20distribute%20them%3F%20TelevisaUnivision%20has%20its%20own%20platforms%20to%20post%20such%20shows.%20But%20production%20companies%20that%20don't%20have%20their%20own%20distribution%20arms%20could%20use%20the%20likes%20of%20TikTok%20or%20YouTube%20and%20share%20the%20revenue%20with%20the%20platform.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAre%20these%20dramas%20too%20far%20out%20of%20Hollywood's%20comfort%20zone%20for%20it%20to%20get%20right%3F%20Hollywood%20insiders%20remember%20how%20Quibi%2C%20Jeffrey%20Katzenberg's%20idea%20to%20make%20quick-bite%20shows%2C%20went%20down%20in%20ignominy.%20The%20big%20difference%20is%20that%20Quibi's%20episodes%20were%20more%20highly%20produced%20than%20today's%20vertical%20dramas%20and%20didn't%20employ%20a%20%26quot%3Bfreemium%2C%26quot%3B%20pay-as-you-go%20model.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a2181936-e089-4df3-97cd-230b67e58359%5C%22%3E'It's%20just%20a%20matter%20of%20time'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Mean%20Girls%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F683a2bef6ffb6822ec61d8b1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EParamount's%20%26quot%3BMean%20Girls%26quot%3B%20experiment%20on%20TikTok%20bore%20some%20resemblance%20to%20mini-dramas.%3Cp%3EParamount%20Pictures%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20media%20insiders%2