n%3ETech%20workers%20on%20Blind%20say%20that%20morale%20at%20Mark%20Zuckerberg's%20Meta%20is%20especially%20terrible%20right%20now.%3Cp%3EEmma%20McIntyre%2FWireImage%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20moved%20from%20Amazon%20to%20Microsoft%20because%20the%20PIP%20culture%20at%20Amazon%20completely%20burned%20me%20out%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20Blinder%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BThe%20whole%20thing%20really%20messed%20with%20me%20mentally%2C%20and%20I%20promised%20myself%20I'd%20never%20go%20through%20something%20like%20that%20again.%20Fast%20forward%20to%20today%20and%20Microsoft%20is%20now%20rolling%20out%20PIP.%26quot%3B%20The%20poster%20despaired%20of%20ever%20being%20free%20of%20the%20constant%20scrutiny.%20%26quot%3BDo%20you%20need%20to%20go%20to%20a%20fucking%20startup%20or%20something%3F%3F%26quot%3B%20they%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20pile-on%20began.%20Some%20accused%20the%20Blinder%20of%20being%20a%20subpar%20coder%20who%20was%20too%20inflexible%20to%20take%20criticism.%20Others%20then%20accused%20those%20Blinders%20of%20being%20managers%20who%20were%20too%20insecure%20to%20acknowledge%20that%20PIPs%20are%20destroying%20the%20spirit%20of%20teamwork%20that%20attracted%20so%20many%20workers%20to%20the%20tech%20industry.%20It%20felt%20like%20every%20other%20social%20media%20platform%3A%20a%20toxic%20stew%20of%20mistrust%20and%20recrimination.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20thing%20almost%20everyone%20seemed%20to%20agree%20on%3F%20That%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-layoffs-low-performance-cuts-review-cycle-politics-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emorale%20is%20especially%20terrible%20at%20Meta%20right%20now.%3C%2Fa%3E%20%26quot%3BWe%20are%20all%20hired%20mercenaries%20chasing%20high%20TC%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20Meta%20employee%20lamented.%20Others%20complained%20about%20grueling%20hours%20and%20what%20they%20see%20as%20a%20culture%20of%20backstabbing.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20at%20Meta%2C