quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20uncorked%20a%20truly%20vile%20tirade%20against%20%26quot%3BIndian%20women%20managers.%26quot%3B%20it%20ranged%20from%20stereotyping%20about%20people%20who%20are%20%26quot%3Bfresh%20off%20the%20boat%26quot%3B%20to%20derogatory%20speculation%20about%20their%20love%20lives%20to%20outright%20calling%20them%20%26quot%3Boverweight%20and%20ugly.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20another%20post%2C%20a%20Blinder%20from%20Adobe%20asked%20a%20workplace%20etiquette%20question.%20%26quot%3BCo-worker%20brings%20Indian%20food%20to%20desk%20and%20whole%20aisle%20smells%20like%20food%2C%26quot%3B%20they%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BHow%20to%20be%20respectful%20and%20say%20no%20to%20this%20habit%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20Blinder%20from%20Pinterest%20tried%20to%20step%20in.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20going%20to%20assume%20that%20this%20question%20was%20asked%20in%20good%20faith%2C%26quot%3B%20they%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BBut%20next%20time%20rather%20than%20pointing%20out%20the%20cuisine%20specifically%2C%20just%20say%20that%20they%20brought%20'ethnic%20food'%20to%20the%20office%20and%20the%20smell%20is%20particularly%20strong.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETheir%20heart%20was%20in%20the%20right%20place%20%E2%80%94%20or%20at%20least%20near%20it.%20But%20the%20next%20exchange%20obliterated%20any%20goodwill%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EApple%3C%2Fem%3E%3A%20Bring%20big%20fat%20beef%20steak%20%2C%20and%20make%20sure%20to%20eat%20in%20front%20of%20him%20loudly%20%E2%80%A6%20He%20will%20stop%20eating%20at%20desk%20afterwards.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EInstacart%3C%2Fem%3E%3A%20Stop%20overreacting%20you%20pos.%20You%20can%20eat%20fish%2C%20beef%20and%20all%20the%20crap%20that%20stinks%20but%20it's%20only%20Indian%20food%20that%20bothers%20you.%20Prick.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ECorum%3C%2Fem%3E%3A%20You%20are%20the%20one%20overreacting.%20The%20OP%20asked%20the%20question%20respectfully.%20Indian%20food%20is%20really%20pungent%20compared%20to%20a%20ham%20sandwich.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20sense%2C%20'twas%20ever%20thus.%20Silicon%20Valley%20has%20long%20struggled%20with%20racism%20and%20misogyny.%20As%20those%20sociologists%20wrote%2C%20modern%20tech%20was%20founded%20in%20part%20on%20%26quot%3Ban%20exploitative%20guest%20worker%20program%20that%20prioritized%20entry%20for%20East%20and%20South%20Asian%20engineers%20starting%20in%20the%201960s.%26quot%3B%20But%20the%20Blind%20I%20remembered%20didn't%20indulge%20in%20X-style%20hyperpolarization.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20the%20shrapnel%20explodes%20in%20all%20directions.%20Men%20on%20Blind%20accuse%20each%20other%20of%20lying%20about%20how%20much%20they%20exercise%2C%20and%20how%20many%20women%20they%20have%20sex%20with.%20Men%20who%20claim%20to%20be%20of%20Indian%20descent%20ask%20other%20Indian%20men%20how%20to%20deal%20with%20their%20white%20American%20wives%20who%20want%20to%20have%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBlind's%20recent%20growth%20has%20also%20come%20from%20more%20women%20joining%20the%20network%20%E2%80%94%20and%20for%20them%2C%20this%20nonsense%20is%20exhausting.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20choose%20a%20career%20you%20are%20a%20feminist%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20worker%20from%20Amazon%20posted%20in%20a%20channel%20called%20Women%20in%20Core%20Tech.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20don't%20have%20a%20career%20you%20are%20a%20gold%20digger.%20If%20you%20have%20an%20opinion%20you%20are%20argumentative%2C%20if%20you%20don't%20have%20one%20you%20are%20boring.%20It's%20like%20they%20were%20expecting%20pets%20and%20don't%20know%20how%20to%20deal%20with%20an%20entire%20other%20gender%20of%20humans.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20few%20men%20replied%20sympathetically%20%E2%80%94%20sorry%20you're%20dealing%20with%20this%2C%20it%20sucks%2C%20etc.%20They%20got%20called%20simps.%20A%20Googler%20responded%20with%20a%20chart%20from%20the%20Financial%20Times%20showing%20a%20global%20divergence%20in%20politics%20between%20men%20(who%20are%20growing%20more%20conservative)%20and%20women%20(who%20are%20growing%20more%20liberal).%20The%20Googler%20cited%20it%20as%20evidence%20that%20women%20have%20taken%20up%20%26quot%3Bwoke%20moral%20purity%20as%20a%20substitute%20for%20religion.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20going%20has%20gotten%20tough%20in%20tech.%20Things%20are%20falling%20apart.%20Today%2C%20the%20open%2C%20communal%20vibe%20I%20encountered%20on%20Blind%20back%20in%202022%20seems%20like%20a%20relic%20of%20some%20long-forgetten%20age.%20A%20spokesperson%20for%20the%20network%20tells%20me%20that%2C%20according%20to%20their%20data%2C%20the%20percentage%20of%20posts%20that%20use%20discriminatory%20language%20has%20actually%20decreased%20slightly%20since%202022.%20But%20the%20overall%20volume%20of%20posts%20has%20grown%2C%20so%20%26quot%3Bthe%20absolute%20number%20of%20problematic%20posts%20may%20rise.%26quot%3B%20Whatever%20the%20math%2C%20I%20was%20heartbroken%20to%20see%20that%20Blind%2C%20too%2C%20has%20gone%20feral.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20boom%20days%20of%20tech%2C%20the%20platform's%20homepage%20used%20to%20have%20a%20running%20ticker%20in%20the%20upper%20right%20corner%20cycling%20through%20a%20list%20of%20current%20job%20openings%2C%20many%20of%20which%20offered%20remarkably%20high%20levels%20of%20compensation.%20It%20seemed%20like%20both%20goal%20and%20enticement%2C%20a%20mutually%20agreed-upon%20brass%20ring%20for%20those%20who%20had%20decided%20to%20make%20a%20career%20in%20tech.%20Now%20the%20ticker%2C%20along%20with%20many%20of%20the%20jobs%20it%20used%20to%20list%2C%20is%20gone.%20For%20Blinders%2C%20all%20that's%20left%20is%20a%20dystopian%20cesspool%20of%20snark%20%E2%80%94%20most%20of%20it%20directed%20not%20at%20the%20external%20forces%20reshaping%20their%20livelihoods%2C%20but%20at%20one%20another.%20For%20millions%20of%20beleaguered%2C%20burned-out%20users%2C%20it's%20one%20more%20indignity%20to%20bear%20as%20they%20struggle%20to%20hang%20on%20to%20what%20little%20hope%20they%20have%20left.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Faut